{
  "texts": [
    "This requires determination of [LB i,UB i] ∀i=1,•••,256 bounds.",
    "Additionally, let us assume that only 3 out of the 8 dependent actuators are nearest neighbours, w.r.t.",
    "sensor s. Using GiBy, we would have only considered nearest neighbour (2foot_2 = 8) actuation states, and determined [LB j,UB j] ∀ j=1,•••,8.",
    "As a result, there was no change in the overall state sensor bounds (safety limits) determined, although some detection resolution was lost by considering only the nearest neighbours.Another limitation expected from the anomaly detector is a sensitivity to out of bound measurements, resulting in warnings being issued when no attack is present.",
    "This limitation could occur even in the system normal (initial) operating phase."
  ]
}